modules.description: This module directly represents HTML as an AST with elements, text, attributes, and raw content. It supports building and manipulating HTML trees using types like `t` for nodes, including element constructors, text nodes, and splices for list-like structures. Use it to generate HTML programmatically with precise control over structure and attributes, especially when composing complex or dynamic content.

This module offers functions to create and manipulate HTML attributes with type-safe constructors, supporting string, integer, and boolean values. It provides common attributes like `href`, `id`, `tabindex`, and `disabled`, along with utilities for optional attributes and numeric values. Designed for safe HTML generation, it ensures proper escaping of UTF-8 encoded content while allowing dynamic attribute assembly in element construction workflows.

This module enables construction of HTML elements and fragments, including text nodes, void elements, and structured tags, using functions that follow consistent naming conventions. It operates on a typed representation of HTML content, supporting operations like rendering to strings, assembling full pages, and low-level AST manipulation through specialized combinators. Designed for programmatic HTML generation, it ensures safe data escaping while requiring UTF-8 input, and is suited for building semantic web interfaces, dynamic document assembly, and structured markup workflows.

This module provides functions for generating HTML content through two main components: `At` creates and manipulates type-safe HTML attributes with support for strings, integers, and booleans, handling common attributes and optional values. `El` constructs HTML elements and fragments, including text nodes and void elements, with rendering capabilities for full pages or structured markup. It is used for building semantic web interfaces, dynamic HTML assembly, and safe programmatic generation of documents with proper data escaping.
